## Summary of Open Items, subSessionId, and Session Spawning

Based on my thorough search of the codebase, here are all the key components related to open items and session spawning:

### 1. **DB Schema for Open Items**

**File:** `/Users/stephanostsoucas/gossamer/prisma/schema.prisma` (Lines 171-181)

```prisma
model OpenItem {
  id                            Int                       @id @default(autoincrement())
  checkpointSessionSummaryId    Int
  checkpointSessionSummary      CheckpointSessionSummary @relation(fields: [checkpointSessionSummaryId], references: [id])
  text                          String
  status                        String                    @default("open") // "open" | "in_progress" | "complete"
  subSessionId                  String?

  @@unique([checkpointSessionSummaryId, text])
  @@index([checkpointSessionSummaryId])
}
```

The `OpenItem` model has:
- `id`: auto-incrementing primary key
- `text`: the open item description
- `status`: tracks state as "open" | "in_progress" | "complete"
- `subSessionId`: optional link to a child session that was spawned for this item

### 2. **Populating Open Items from Checkpoints**

**File:** `/Users/stephanostsoucas/gossamer/src/indexer.ts` (Lines 469-486)

```typescript
if (sm.open_items?.length) {
